ai.skymind.pipelines.pipeline.handlers.converter

Interface JsonArrayConverter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseJsonArrayConverter, JsonArrayMapConverter

    public interface JsonArrayConverter
    An interface for converting input json arrays of either arrays of arrays (csvs) or arrays of objects/dictionaries converting the input to either pmml oriented dictionary output or datavec oriented arrow batches.
    Author:
    Adam Gibson

    • Method Detail

      • convertPmmlWithErrors

        org.nd4j.linalg.primitives.Pair<Map<Integer,Integer>,List<? extends Map<org.dmg.pmml.FieldName,?>>> convertPmmlWithErrors(org.datavec.api.transform.schema.Schema schema,
                                                                                                                          io.vertx.core.json.JsonArray jsonArray,
                                                                                                                          DataPipelineErrorHandler dataPipelineErrorHandler)
        Convert a json array of arrays to the proper format for pmml. PMML expects a list of named tuples where each name is a FieldName representing a column in the input. This returns a mapping of original indices to the output indices. If there are no errors,mappings should be 1 to 1. If there were errors, the map is used to find what rows in the output (the second part of the pair) map to the original input rows.
        Parameters:
        schema - the inputSchema for the input
        jsonArray - the array of arrays to use
        dataPipelineErrorHandler - the DataPipelineErrorHandler when an error is encountered in the conversion step
        Returns:
        a map of the original inputs to the output rows, and the list of converted inputs in pmml format

      • convert

        org.datavec.arrow.recordreader.ArrowWritableRecordBatch convert(org.datavec.api.transform.schema.Schema schema,
                                                                io.vertx.core.json.JsonArray jsonArray)
        Convert a JsonArray given an input inputSchema to an ArrowWritableRecordBatch representing a schemaed input for use with nd4j based pipelines where data in memory is represented by arrow. The ArrowWritableRecordBatch is an implementation of the expected input format for org.deeplearning4j.datasets.datavec.RecordReaderDataSetIterator Record
        Parameters:
        schema - the input inputSchema to use
        jsonArray - the json array of raw data to convert
        Returns:
        the converted batch

      • convertWithErrors

        org.nd4j.linalg.primitives.Pair<Map<Integer,Integer>,org.datavec.arrow.recordreader.ArrowWritableRecordBatch> convertWithErrors(org.datavec.api.transform.schema.Schema schema,
                                                                                                                                io.vertx.core.json.JsonArray jsonArray,

        Convert a json array of arrays to ArrowWritableRecordBatch. This returns a mapping of original indices to the output indices. If there are no errors,mappings should be 1 to 1. If there were errors, the map is used to find what rows in the output (the second part of the pair) map to the original input rows.
        Parameters:

        jsonArray - the array of arrays to use
        dataPipelineErrorHandler - the DataPipelineErrorHandler when an error is encountered in the conversion step
        Returns:
        a map of the original inputs to the output rows, and the ArrowWritableRecordBatch resulting from the conversion
